        titulo: "Action or Omission",
        texto: "Beloved ones! Many of you have questioned about two daily attitudes that bring some doubts regarding acting or not in certain situations. Despite the interest in increasingly understanding the role of each human being currently incarnated on Earth, as one understands how life is seen from a spiritual perspective, it seems that the more one knows, the less one is knowing. Many messages tell us that there are no mistakes, but what there actually is, is always learning. So, if we sin through acts and also by omission, obviously, we also learn through such attitudes. It seems like a paradox, but it is very difficult to separate the same action into two directions, for it can be both positive and negative. If we sin by acts or omission, we can also do good deeds through them. So where is the difference? Well, I would say it can only be in the intention. Many times we have already said here that everything is in the intention. It is the key that opens both the door to the Light and the door that leads to darkness. Therefore, when someone asks me how to know if they are on the path of ascension, I answer that I do not know, for if everything is in the intention, how could I know the intention of each one, in each act, action or intention? The answer also serves for those who say they do not know how to act in certain situations. Always do everything with the intention of good and everything will be well done. Even if the result is not as expected, at least you will have done everything that was yours to do. And this simplifies everything. Life is not complicated, what complicates is the interest that each one puts in each situation. Knowing when we should act or abstain is a matter of wisdom, not a matter of competence. And if we act with wisdom, then it is certain that we will not interfere with the free will of others. This is another key that we should never forget. By acting with good intention, we will be putting compassion and unconditional love into practice. And if we act only by guiding, we are respecting the free choice of the other. We should never make the choice for others! We should also not impose conditions or our will. Some even say they want to change the other or, at least, ardently hope that the other changes according to their convictions. This is nothing more than a pretense and, as such, is useless. There are many ways to learn and each one has their own. Helping when we are asked is still the best choice on our part. Making instructions available to those who are interested, without, however, expecting everyone to appreciate such devices is also a way to help without interfering with free will. As for omission, we can make the same parameter here in relation to actions. If we abstain when we actually have an opportunity to help someone, we are incurring in a lack of charity. Knowing when to speak up or when to abstain is also a demonstration of wisdom. Remember that wisdom and knowledge are not the same thing. Many times, omission is necessary and much more useful than action. For example, telling something to someone, whose information will trigger unnecessary pain and suffering, or will promote intrigues, arguments, revolt or revenge, besides the discord and hatred derived from all this. Abstaining can be the best choice in many situations. On the contrary, abstaining when we have an opportunity to help is a selfish act and generates reactions according to the Law of Cause and Effect. As we can see, the line that separates the positive and the negative of each attitude to be taken is really very thin. And, to make decision-making even more difficult, we need to take into account that others are also students of this school of souls and each one is at their own level of learning. In this school no one can take the tests for others. There is no cheating or any trick that can facilitate the climb of the soul's ascension ladder. When we remember the Divine Law, which says that no one will go through what they do not need to go through, it becomes easier to understand the other and also easier to know when we should act or abstain. Always remember that what works for you may not work for the other and vice versa. There are no two consciousnesses on the same step of the ladder. We are doing well in this final stretch of the long journey of life and, despite the illusory appearances of the 3D mind, we see great changes in consciousness in a good part of humanity. Incredible times bring all the necessary opportunities now. Watching and praying also serve those who want to take advantage of every opportunity to elevate themselves. The moment is no longer for the clever, but for the awakened. Use your wisdom and simplify your life and the lives of others as well. Namaste!",
